{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":26697,"name":"","username":"Hideman","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/h/a87d85/{size}.png","created_at":"2018-11-26T16:57:16.332Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eHi everyone,\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI just want to known how we can get the maximum texture size to build a texture atlas on the fly and save it on disk?\u003cbr\u003e\nTexture atlas need to be generate manually because I want to support modding with custom texture for additional game objects.\u003cbr\u003e\nAnd finally if you have links to some discussions or anything about texture atlas creation on the fly with Urho3D I will be appreciate it very well.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eTks for your further response.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2018-11-26T16:57:16.332Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":9,"reads":36,"readers_count":35,"score":52.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":4695,"topic_slug":"how-find-the-maximum-texture-size-supported","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":1073,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":26698,"name":"Justin Miller","username":"jmiller","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/jmiller/{size}/2367_2.png","created_at":"2018-11-26T18:16:25.385Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eHi,\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eMaximum texture size depends primarily on the graphics hardware.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWildfire offered a dataset:\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003ca href=\"https://feedback.wildfiregames.com/report/opengl/feature/GL_MAX_TEXTURE_SIZE\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003ehttps://feedback.wildfiregames.com/report/opengl/feature/GL_MAX_TEXTURE_SIZE\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/19572659/is-1024x1024-a-widely-supported-opengl-maximum-texture-size-on-the-desktop\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003ehttps://stackoverflow.com/questions/19572659/is-1024x1024-a-widely-supported-opengl-maximum-texture-size-on-the-desktop\u003c/a\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nMaybe the 1024 is a bit outdated.\u003cbr\u003e\nOther articles will go into more detail about specific devices‚Ä¶\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAlso, maybe some users have dropped some info on how they setup their \u003ca href=\"https://discourse.urho3d.io/search?q=texture%20atlas\" data-bbcode=\"true\"\u003etexture atlas\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIf one need make engine modifications to check max size, I only speculate that the internal \u003ccode\u003eSDLRenderer-\u0026gt;info.max_texture_width\u003c/code\u003e (+height) may hold the API-agnostic answer‚Ä¶\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2018-11-30T21:09:50.361Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":36,"readers_count":35,"score":12.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":4695,"topic_slug":"how-find-the-maximum-texture-size-supported","display_username":"Justin Miller","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":4,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://feedback.wildfiregames.com/report/opengl/feature/GL_MAX_TEXTURE_SIZE","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"OpenGL capabilities report: GL_MAX_TEXTURE_SIZE","clicks":4},{"url":"https://discourse.urho3d.io/search?q=texture%20atlas","internal":true,"reflection":false,"clicks":2},{"url":"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/19572659/is-1024x102